TITLE: NASA delays Artemis moon mission after second launch attempt halted due to fuel leak
SUMMARY: NASA is postponing its Artemis I launch again, after making a second attempt to get the mission off the ground on Saturday.

TITLE: EU economics chief says bloc is not afraid of Putin, ready to react over halted Russian gas supplies
SUMMARY: The European Union is "ready to react" to Russia's latest decision to halt gas supplies to the bloc, a top EU official has told CNBC.

TITLE: 'Why shouldn't it be as bad as the 1970s?': Historian Niall Ferguson has a warning for investors
SUMMARY: Niall Ferguson warned Friday that the world is sleepwalking into an era of political and economic upheaval akin to the 1970s — only worse.

TITLE: This couple had an Amazon-themed wedding to celebrate how e-commerce brought them together
SUMMARY: Eddie Levine and Jing Gao tied the knot on Aug. 21, and planned their wedding reception to pay homage to their roots in online retail.

TITLE: New omicron boosters are now available, but it's unclear how effective they will be
SUMMARY: Top health officials believe the shots will provide more durable protection against Covid, but acknowledge it's not yet clear just how effective they will be.

TITLE: Sen. Lindsey Graham says he was stating the obvious with Trump riots claim
SUMMARY: U.S. Senator Lindsey Graham has defended saying there would be "riots in the streets" if Trump was prosecuted for mishandling classified information.

TITLE: 'Climate disaster of biblical proportions': Pakistan minister warns flood damage will exceed $10 billion
SUMMARY: Already reeling from an economic crisis, flood waters have submerged over one third of the country in water, killing over 1,000 and impacting 33 million people.

TITLE: This $30 mouse jiggler makes it look like you're working when you're not
SUMMARY: I recently bought a mouse jiggler to trick my computer into thinking I'm online. Here's what I thought.

TITLE: Google Flights just busted a popular myth about saving money on flights
SUMMARY: Google Flights examined five years of historical flight data to reveal the strategies that save money on airfare.

TITLE: Comcast executives expect Disney to stick to its agreement to acquire the remaining stake in Hulu
SUMMARY: Disney and Comcast have an existing arrangement in which Disney will acquire Comcast's 33% stake in Hulu in 2024.

TITLE: G-7 nations back plan to cap Russian oil prices in a bid to drain the Kremlin’s war chest
SUMMARY: The Group of Seven wealthy nations on Friday agreed to implement a price-capping mechanism on Russian oil exports.

TITLE: Payrolls rose 315,000 in August as companies keep hiring
SUMMARY: Nonfarm payrolls were expected to increase 318,000 in August, according to Dow Jones estimates.

TITLE: Huawei spin-off Honor to launch first foldable phone abroad as Chinese firm takes on Apple, Samsung
SUMMARY: Honor launched the Honor 70 in Europe on Friday and said it will release its first foldable overseas as it looks to boost its international smartphone sales.

TITLE: Economist Joseph Stiglitz says there are 3 reasons why further Fed rate hikes might make inflation worse
SUMMARY: The Nobel Prize-winning economist said aggressive monetary tightening would not just fail to alleviate supply-chain pressures but worsen them.

TITLE: The Fed must do two things to re-establish credibility, Allianz's El-Erian says
SUMMARY: The U.S. Federal Reserve needs to do two more things to re-establish its credibility, according to Mohamed El-Erian, chief economic adviser to Allianz.

TITLE: PGA Tour denies renewal of membership for LIV-affiliated players
SUMMARY: The PGA Tour has denied the renewal of tour memberships for LIV-affiliated players.

TITLE: Starbucks names Laxman Narasimhan as new CEO, starting in April
SUMMARY: Narasimhan will join Starbucks in October, learning about the company and its reinvention plan, before assuming the top job in April.

TITLE: Energy CEO calls out Europe's 'foolish' dependence on natural gas
SUMMARY: Francesco Starace was speaking to CNBC at the Ambrosetti Forum in Italy.

TITLE: China's electric car firms, which rely heavily on Nvidia, are safe from the U.S. chip ban — for now
SUMMARY: U.S. restrictions on Nvidia chip sales to China won't affect Chinese electric car companies.

TITLE: China's e-commerce giant Pinduoduo quietly launches U.S. shopping site in Amazon challenge
SUMMARY: Pinduoduo launched its U.S. online shopping site Temu as the Chinese e-commerce giant makes its first major push overseas.

TITLE: Russia could be like 'North Korea on steroids' when Putin is replaced, former Kremlin advisor says
SUMMARY: Economist Sergei Guriev on Friday warned that Russia could become like "North Korea on steroids" when President Vladimir Putin is replaced.

TITLE: Britain's banks are giving staff one-off crisis payments. But they're being urged to do much more
SUMMARY: UK banks offered employees one-time bonuses or pay increases to help with the cost of living, but longer-term solutions may be needed to keep hold of staff.

TITLE: Chinese stocks could plunge by 20% if real estate troubles get much worse, Morgan Stanley says
SUMMARY: China's real estate problems could significantly drag down the economy and stocks if authorities don't provide enough support, Morgan Stanley analysts said.

TITLE: Nvidia says U.S. government allows A.I. chip development in China
SUMMARY: Nvidia said Thursday that the U.S. government told it that it can continue to develop its H100 artificial intelligence chip in China.

TITLE: Turkey's skyrocketing inflation is flashing warning signals for Gulf banks
SUMMARY: Ratings agency Fitch calculates that GCC banks with Turkish subsidiaries posted net losses of roughly $950 million in the first half of 2022.

TITLE: Critical August jobs report expected to run hot and that could lead to a more aggressive Fed
SUMMARY: Job growth likely slowed from July's frenzied pace, but is still expected to have been quite strong in August, with broad-based hiring across many sectors.

TITLE: Lukoil Chairman Ravil Maganov is the 8th Russian energy executive to die suddenly this year
SUMMARY: Since January, seven other Russian energy executives have died under unusual circumstances, according to reports by Russian and international news agencies.

TITLE: 'Quiet quitting' isn't always the best option — try these 3 things first, experts say
SUMMARY: While quiet quitting may help to ease burnout in the short-term, it is not a long-term solution, workplace experts tell CNBC Make It.

TITLE: Partnership with traditional retailers is the way to go for online businesses, Lazada CEO says
SUMMARY: Alibaba-owned Lazada said that most, if not all offline players, should be partners with it, to serve all the needs of consumers.

TITLE: Amazon took all U.S. solar rooftops offline last year after flurry of fires, electrical explosions
SUMMARY: While Amazon tries to go green, the company has encountered numerous challenges with solar panels at various warehouses.
